6. DATA PROTECTION & PRIVACY

The Software is designed in compliance with the Digital Personal Data
Protection (DPDP) Act, 2023 of India. The following data principles are
enforced at the architectural level:

(a) DATA MINIMIZATION: The Software collects and processes only the minimum
    data necessary for its intended purpose. No personally identifiable
    information (PII) such as real names, email addresses, or phone numbers
    is stored in the system.

(b) PURPOSE LIMITATION: All data collected is used solely for the purpose
    of providing student wellbeing services. Data is not used for marketing,
    profiling, or any secondary purpose.

(c) STORAGE LIMITATION: Student identification data (APAAR IDs, ERP IDs)
    is processed transiently and stored only as one-way cryptographic hashes.
    Raw identification data is never persisted.

(d) CONSENT: The Software implements granular cookie consent mechanisms and
    provides transparency about data processing practices.

(e) RIGHT TO ERASURE: End Users may request account deletion through their
    institutional coordinator (SPOC). The Software supports complete data
    removal upon authorized request.

(f) SECURITY: All sensitive data is encrypted at rest and in transit.
    Row-Level Security (RLS) policies enforce data isolation between
    institutions and users.

The Licensor shall not be liable for data protection violations arising
from the Licensee's failure to comply with applicable data protection laws
in their jurisdiction.

================================================================================

7. AI & SAFETY SYSTEMS

The Software includes AI-powered safety monitoring features. These systems:

(a) Are designed to ASSIST human decision-making, not replace it

(b) Generate suggestions and risk assessments that require human review
    and approval before any action is taken

(c) Do not store full audio recordings — only brief snippets (±10 seconds)
    are captured when a human operator explicitly triggers an escalation

(d) All AI-generated assessments and human responses are logged for
    accountability and audit purposes

The Licensor makes no warranty regarding the accuracy or completeness of
AI-generated risk assessments. The Licensee acknowledges that final
responsibility for clinical decisions rests with qualified human
professionals.

